node_modules/
dist/
# The GitHub Action ships a committed, self-contained bundle so it can run via
# `uses:` without a node_modules install. Track only that one bundle file; the
# rest of the action's dist/ and every other package's dist/ stay ignored.
# (Re-include the dir non-recursively first so a file negation inside it can win.)
!packages/action/dist/
packages/action/dist/*
!packages/action/dist/index.js
*.tsbuildinfo
.DS_Store
coverage/
*.log
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
